body:
If there is a package (named, or the $unit package) which contains static variables (explicit or in functions/tasks), then when hierarchically verilating the design, each library module will have it's own copy of those statics. e.g in hierarchical mode, there will be 2 global_counters instead of one, each incrementing independent of the other:

```systemverilog

// in $unit
int global_counter;

module top(input wire clk);
   sub sub(clk);
   always (@posedge clk) global_counter += 1;
endmodule

module sub(input wire clk);
   /* verilator hier_block */
   always (@posedge clk) global_counter += 1;
endmodule
```

Bit of a corner case, but probably warrants a warning/unsupported (static state in package with --lib-crate). However this can arise more easily with static vars in functions in the package.

Same applies with --lib-create instead of --hierarchical.

Just recording for reference.

